parameters: Kru: "There are fewer monsters than I thought."
Kru: "What's wrong, Umi? Are you tired?"
Banka: "Umi-san. Kru is asking if you're tired..."
Umi: "Ah... *pant* *pant*... I understand. Maybe I'm a little... tired..."
Banka: "Umi-san seems to be having a hard time."
Kru: "Hey Banka! She said it tickles, didn't she?"

Banka: "No, you see. It feels really nice to touch. It's soft and
pleasant."
Kru: "It feels even better than before..."

Banka: "They say it becomes more lively depending on the user's life
force."
Umi: "Uuu... stop it already... let go..."
Kru: "Hey Banka! You're taking your pranks too far."
Banka: "My apologies, I got carried away."
Kru: "Umi? Are you okay? It seems like it's more than just ticklish..."
Umi: "It's not like that! It's just ticklish!"
Banka: "Ahaha... I bet that's really ticklish... Shall we move on now?"
Kru: "But Umi, you should stay here and rest."

Kru: "You're actually feeling unwell, right? Your cheeks wouldn't be so red
just from being ticklish."
Banka: "As expected of Kru. I didn't notice."
Kru: "Banka. I'm going to go ahead alone. Take care of Umi for me."
Kru: "Banka. I'm counting on you to look after Umi."
Kru: "It's okay! I'll be back soon."
Banka: "It seems like Umi-san has accumulated some fatigue..."
Kru: "Umi... Are you alright? You look spaced out..."
Banka: "She probably got too excited from the adventure she's not used to."
Kru: "Hey, Umi? Are you sure you're okay?"
Umi: "Huh? Oh... Kru. Yeah... I'm fine..."

Kru: "That's good to hear. It's all over now, let's go home. Thanks,
Banka."
